<p>Before flying, check whether your location falls within controlled, restricted or sensitive airspace. Additional conditions may apply even where operations are otherwise permitted.</p>
<h2>Area categories</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Controlled aerodrome zones:</strong> Coordinate with relevant authorities and comply with published constraints.</li>
  <li><strong>Critical infrastructure zones:</strong> Power, transport and communications sites may have protective restrictions.</li>
  <li><strong>Temporary event restrictions:</strong> Public events, state ceremonies and emergency operations can trigger temporary controls.</li>
  <li><strong>Environmental protection areas:</strong> Seasonal limits may protect wildlife and conservation operations.</li>
</ul>
<h2>Operational cautions</h2>
<p>Always plan alternatives, maintain safe standoff distances and discontinue flight where circumstances change and safety margins reduce.</p>
